fs18\cf2 a. The denominator used in estimating the effect sizes. \par Cohen's d uses the pooled standard deviation. \par Hedges' correction uses the pooled standard deviation, plus a correction factor. \par Glass's delta uses the sample standard deviation of the control group.\cell \trowd\trftsWidth3\trwWidth8414\trkeep\trql\trgaph10\trbrdrh\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf0\trbrdrb\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf0\trbrdrv\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf0\trbrdrr\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf0\trbrdrt\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf0\trbrdrl\brdrs\brdrw20\brdrcf0\trpaddl0\trpaddr0\trpaddfl3\trpaddfr3\clvertalt\clcbpat1\clftsWidth3\clwWidth8410\cellx8410\row\pard\pard\plain\sl400\f0 \par \pard\plain\s0\ql\fi0\li0\ri0\plain\f1\fs18\cf0 * Chart Builder.\par GGRAPH\par   /GRAPHDATASET NAME="graphdataset" VARIABLES=GROUP MEANSD(ACCURACY, 2)[name="MEAN_ACCURACY"\par     LOW="MEAN_ACCURACY_LOW" HIGH="MEAN_ACCURACY_HIGH"] MISSING=LISTWISE REPORTMISSING=NO\par   /GRAPHSPEC SOURCE=INLINE.\par BEGIN GPL\par   SOURCE: s=userSource(id("graphdataset"))\par   DATA: GROUP=col(source(s), name("GROUP"), unit.category())\par   DATA: MEAN_ACCURACY=col(source(s), name("MEAN_ACCURACY"))\par   DATA: LOW=col(source(s), name("MEAN_ACCURACY_LOW"))\par   DATA: HIGH=col(source(s), name("MEAN_ACCURACY_HIGH"))\par   GUIDE: axis(dim(1), label("GROUP"))\par   GUIDE: axis(dim(2), label("Mean ACCURACY"))\par   GUIDE: text.title(label("Simple Bar Mean of ACCURACY by GROUP"))\par   GUIDE: text.footnote(label("Error Bars: 95% CI"))\par   GUIDE: text.subfootnote(label("Error Bars: +/- 2 SD"))\par   SCALE: linear(dim(2), include(0))\par   ELEMENT: interval(position(GROUP*MEAN_ACCURACY), shape.interior(shape.square))\par   ELEMENT: interval(position(region.spread.range(GROUP*(LOW+HIGH))), shape.interior(shape.ibeam))\par END GPL.\par \par\pard\plain\sl400\f0 \par \pard\plain\sl400\f0 \par \pard\plain\s0\ql\fi0\li0\ri0\plain\f3\fs20\b\cf0 \par GGraph\par \b0\par\pard\plain\sl400\f0 \par \par\trowd\trftsWidth3\trwWidth6185\trkeep\trql\trgaph10\trbrdrh\brdrs\br